tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows significant renal impairment (markedly elevated creatinine), proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, and abnormal urine appearance, suggesting possible acute or chronic kidney disease with glycosuria not explained by diabetes (very low HbA1c and blood glucose). Urine findings (brown, cloudy, ammoniacal) may indicate underlying renal or urinary tract pathology. Immediate nephrology evaluation is recommended.
